WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.874
CLIFF LUNGARETTI: Hi.

00:00:00.874 --> 00:00:01.800
I'm Cliff Lungaretti.

00:00:01.800 --> 00:00:03.412
Welcome to another
Talk at Google.

00:00:03.412 --> 00:00:05.245
I'm a member of the
Talks at Google program,

00:00:05.245 --> 00:00:06.994
and it's a pleasure
to have you guys here.

00:00:06.994 --> 00:00:09.057
It's also a pleasure to
have Adam Garone, the CEO

00:00:09.057 --> 00:00:11.640
and co-founder of the Movember
Foundation, with us here today.

00:00:11.640 --> 00:00:13.190
So Adam, welcome to Google.

00:00:13.190 --> 00:00:13.470
ADAM GARONE: Thank you.

00:00:13.470 --> 00:00:14.300
Thank you for having us.

00:00:14.300 --> 00:00:15.883
CLIFF LUNGARETTI:
You're very welcome.

00:00:15.883 --> 00:00:17.720
So let's just jump
right into it.

00:00:17.720 --> 00:00:19.650
Let's talk about
Movember and see

00:00:19.650 --> 00:00:22.589
who actually knows
about Movember

00:00:22.589 --> 00:00:24.380
and what we can tell
them out in the world.

00:00:24.380 --> 00:00:27.280
So just as bare
bones as possible.

00:00:27.280 --> 00:00:28.690
ADAM GARONE: Right.

00:00:28.690 --> 00:00:33.610
Yeah, so Movember-- the month
formally known as November--

00:00:33.610 --> 00:00:38.270
it's a campaign to raise funds
and awareness for men's health.

00:00:38.270 --> 00:00:41.770
So three causes that we
fund-- prostate and testicular

00:00:41.770 --> 00:00:46.520
cancers, the two male-only
cancers; and also mental health

00:00:46.520 --> 00:00:47.670
challenges that men face.

00:00:47.670 --> 00:00:49.886
And for the first
time in the US,

00:00:49.886 --> 00:00:52.010
a portion of the funds on
the back of this campaign

00:00:52.010 --> 00:00:53.920
will go to that cause.

00:00:57.130 --> 00:01:01.730
The 101 stuff-- men sign up,
start the month clean shaven,

00:01:01.730 --> 00:01:04.700
grow a mustache for the
30 days, and effectively

00:01:04.700 --> 00:01:08.900
become walking, talking
billboards for men's health.

00:01:08.900 --> 00:01:11.510
And then we have a
Mo Sistas program

00:01:11.510 --> 00:01:15.350
for the women that want to
participate in the campaign.

00:01:15.350 --> 00:01:19.360
A very, very important
part of Movember

00:01:19.360 --> 00:01:22.000
is women that are
often the gatekeepers--

00:01:22.000 --> 00:01:23.090
CLIFF LUNGARETTI: A lot
of Mo Sistas in the house.

00:01:23.090 --> 00:01:24.180
Thank you for joining
us, Mo Sistas.

00:01:24.180 --> 00:01:25.020
ADAM GARONE: Yeah.

00:01:25.020 --> 00:01:27.735
The gatekeepers to
allowing us to grow

00:01:27.735 --> 00:01:29.415
a mustache in the first place.

00:01:29.415 --> 00:01:31.790
CLIFF LUNGARETTI: So Movember's
been around for how long?

00:01:31.790 --> 00:01:32.720
ADAM GARONE: 2003.

00:01:32.720 --> 00:01:33.195
CLIFF LUNGARETTI: 2003.

00:01:33.195 --> 00:01:35.010
And how did Movember
start, since you're

00:01:35.010 --> 00:01:37.296
a co-founder of the
Movember Foundation?

00:01:39.210 --> 00:01:41.420
ADAM GARONE: In sort of
traditional Australian way.

00:01:41.420 --> 00:01:44.740
It was over beers on a
summer afternoon and--

00:01:44.740 --> 00:01:45.955
CLIFF LUNGARETTI: Approved.

00:01:45.955 --> 00:01:47.420
ADAM GARONE: It was
my brother and a mate,

00:01:47.420 --> 00:01:49.035
and they were talking
about fashion.

00:01:50.100 --> 00:01:52.590
And they were
talking about trends

00:01:52.590 --> 00:01:56.280
and how things eventually come
back into style-- and then

00:01:56.280 --> 00:01:58.160
was 2003.

00:01:58.160 --> 00:02:02.580
And the conversation then turned
to what hasn't made a comeback.

00:02:02.580 --> 00:02:07.495
And they could think of two
things-- macrame and mustaches.

00:02:08.820 --> 00:02:11.160
And so our next campaign will
be to bring back macrame.

00:02:12.985 --> 00:02:15.110
A few more beers and the
day ended with a challenge

00:02:15.110 --> 00:02:16.760
to bring back the mustache.

00:02:16.760 --> 00:02:20.680
And really, the initial idea
was to put the mustache back

00:02:20.680 --> 00:02:22.280
on the face of fashion.

00:02:22.280 --> 00:02:25.330
So "mo" is slang for
mustache in Australia,

00:02:25.330 --> 00:02:27.490
so the month was renamed.

00:02:27.490 --> 00:02:31.170
And 30 of us
participated in 2003.

00:02:31.170 --> 00:02:36.140
And we were literally the only
late 20-year-old, 30-year-old

00:02:36.140 --> 00:02:38.930
guys rocking
mustaches back then.

00:02:38.930 --> 00:02:43.770
And the response
was amazing, really,

00:02:43.770 --> 00:02:46.260
and shocking because
people would just

00:02:46.260 --> 00:02:48.630
stop and go, why
are you doing that?

00:02:48.630 --> 00:02:53.060
And boss wouldn't let me go
and see clients and things

00:02:53.060 --> 00:02:53.600
like that.

00:02:53.600 --> 00:02:56.290
And it just generated
so many conversations

00:02:56.290 --> 00:03:00.920
that at the end of the campaign,
the four of us got together

00:03:00.920 --> 00:03:06.120
and we thought, let's
put this toward a cause.

00:03:06.120 --> 00:03:08.419
And we were inspired
by the women around us

00:03:08.419 --> 00:03:10.210
and what they were
doing for breast cancer,

00:03:10.210 --> 00:03:12.760
and just thought there's
nothing for men's health.

00:03:12.760 --> 00:03:17.160
So that became the merger of
the two activities-- growing

00:03:17.160 --> 00:03:19.360
a mustache and men's health.

00:03:19.360 --> 00:03:21.674
CLIFF LUNGARETTI: How much
money did you raise in 2003?

00:03:21.674 --> 00:03:22.590
ADAM GARONE: No money.

00:03:22.590 --> 00:03:23.120
CLIFF LUNGARETTI: No money.

00:03:23.120 --> 00:03:24.036
ADAM GARONE: No money.

00:03:24.036 --> 00:03:26.934
No, it was literally an
excuse to grow a mustache,

00:03:26.934 --> 00:03:28.100
have a mustache [INAUDIBLE].

00:03:28.100 --> 00:03:29.050
CLIFF LUNGARETTI:
When we get to 2004,

00:03:29.050 --> 00:03:30.216
how much money do you raise?

00:03:30.216 --> 00:03:34.230
ADAM GARONE: Yeah,
2004, we had 450 guys

00:03:34.230 --> 00:03:37.730
sign up and participate,
and we raised $54,000.

00:03:37.730 --> 00:03:41.540
And it was the single biggest
donation, the Prostate Cancer

00:03:41.540 --> 00:03:43.700
Foundation in Australia,
had ever received.

00:03:44.970 --> 00:03:48.740
And that year changed our lives.

00:03:48.740 --> 00:03:53.030
And since then, on the back of
all the funds that were raised,

00:03:53.030 --> 00:03:58.230
literally means men's lives have
been impacted by the campaign.

00:03:58.230 --> 00:04:02.320
So yeah, long story short, over
the years, we've had 4 million

00:04:02.320 --> 00:04:03.690
Mo Bros and Mo Sistas sign up.

00:04:03.690 --> 00:04:09.774
We've raised $580 million,
$135 million last year.

00:04:09.774 --> 00:04:11.440
The foundation is now
the biggest funder

00:04:11.440 --> 00:04:15.562
of prostate and testicular
cancer research in the world.

00:04:15.562 --> 00:04:18.527
So yeah, it's been
an amazing journey.

00:04:18.527 --> 00:04:19.610
CLIFF LUNGARETTI: Awesome.

00:04:19.610 --> 00:04:21.089
Well, it's great
to have you here.

00:04:21.089 --> 00:04:23.050
And actually, I'm not going
to throw it to a video

00:04:23.050 --> 00:04:24.925
as now that we've
discussed what is Movember,

00:04:24.925 --> 00:04:27.500
we're going to just show a
little shiny thing if we could.

00:04:27.500 --> 00:04:29.390
Let you have a glass of water.

00:04:29.390 --> 00:04:29.890
All right.

00:04:29.890 --> 00:04:31.220
So if we can cue that up, Dave.

00:04:31.220 --> 00:04:31.913
Thanks, man.

