segments of the community.

00:14:04.770 --> 00:14:07.300
So if you look at the
military, more men

00:14:07.300 --> 00:14:11.630
have taken their lives after
serving in Iraq and Afghanistan

00:14:11.630 --> 00:14:13.010
than died in the battlefield.

00:14:14.250 --> 00:14:17.770
And that is a shocking outcome.

00:14:17.770 --> 00:14:21.370
And again, it's a
really complex issue.

00:14:21.370 --> 00:14:24.470
With prostate and
testicular cancer,

00:14:24.470 --> 00:14:28.230
we're on the path to effectively
curing both of those diseases.

00:14:28.230 --> 00:14:31.540
And what we mean by that is
we will soon be at a stage

00:14:31.540 --> 00:14:35.320
where no man should die from
either of those diseases.

00:14:35.320 --> 00:14:41.310
For sure, if a guy doesn't
present and he's got an issue,

00:14:41.310 --> 00:14:42.890
he will pass from
testicular cancer.

00:14:42.890 --> 00:14:44.590
There's no doubt about that.

00:14:44.590 --> 00:14:47.040
But through ongoing
awareness, education,

00:14:47.040 --> 00:14:50.400
getting guys going
to the doctor,

00:14:50.400 --> 00:14:53.030
there's one last piece of the
puzzle with testicular cancer,

00:14:53.030 --> 00:14:58.150
and we've just launched a
global collaborative research

00:14:58.150 --> 00:14:59.980
initiative to the tune
of about $3 million,

00:14:59.980 --> 00:15:03.704
bringing together the
best minds to solve

00:15:03.704 --> 00:15:04.870
that last bit of the puzzle.

00:15:04.870 --> 00:15:07.310
And then it'll
effectively be cured.

00:15:07.310 --> 00:15:11.300
Prostate cancer is a
more complex disease.

00:15:11.300 --> 00:15:15.140
We help fund at the
University of Michigan

00:15:15.140 --> 00:15:19.380
the identification of 28
types of prostate cancer.

00:15:20.860 --> 00:15:24.470
And we know of those prostate
cancers which are aggressive,

00:15:24.470 --> 00:15:27.720
and it's about 20% of them
are aggressive and need

00:15:27.720 --> 00:15:28.520
radical treatment.

00:15:28.520 --> 00:15:30.690
So that could be
surgery or radiation.

00:15:30.690 --> 00:15:34.150
But 80% are
slow-growing, indolent,

00:15:34.150 --> 00:15:36.990
and guys can live
with that cancer

00:15:36.990 --> 00:15:39.150
if it stays within the prostate.

00:15:39.150 --> 00:15:43.150
Normally, it's OK.

00:15:43.150 --> 00:15:45.150
The issue at the moment
is with prostate cancer,

00:15:45.150 --> 00:15:47.691
we can't tell a guy definitively
what type of prostate cancer

00:15:47.691 --> 00:15:48.990
he's got.

00:15:48.990 --> 00:15:51.290
So a lot of guys are
rushing in and having

00:15:51.290 --> 00:15:52.300
surgery or radiation.

00:15:53.350 --> 00:15:59.564
And the real issue with
that is the side effects

00:15:59.564 --> 00:16:00.480
from those treatments.

00:16:00.480 --> 00:16:03.470
So it strikes everything
it is to be a man.

00:16:03.470 --> 00:16:06.970
It's like incontinence,
impotence, bowel disorder,

00:16:06.970 --> 00:16:09.710
depression, let alone
the financial burden that

00:16:09.710 --> 00:16:10.410
goes with it.

00:16:10.410 --> 00:16:13.162
So that's the big
contentious issue

00:16:13.162 --> 00:16:14.620
with prostate cancer
at the moment.

00:16:14.620 --> 00:16:16.280
We don't have a
great screening test.

00:16:16.280 --> 00:16:18.940
And there's a lot
of debate around

00:16:18.940 --> 00:16:21.010
should you get screened or not.

00:16:21.010 --> 00:16:25.845
Lot of confusion in the public
and also with GPs around it.

