been sort of structured.

00:17:01.010 --> 00:17:05.470
And it's all around competition,
and they will compete and spend

00:17:05.470 --> 00:17:09.960
so much time putting together
proposals for limited grants,

00:17:09.960 --> 00:17:14.430
and they get notoriety by
getting written up in journals,

00:17:14.430 --> 00:17:18.420
and then more funding
comes off the back of that.

00:17:18.420 --> 00:17:20.839
And it was about
five years ago, we

00:17:20.839 --> 00:17:22.339
were in six countries
at that stage,

00:17:22.339 --> 00:17:25.089
and we didn't [INAUDIBLE]
the research we were doing.

00:17:25.089 --> 00:17:28.540
And there were common
themes and people actually

00:17:28.540 --> 00:17:32.080
researching exactly the same
thing across those countries.

00:17:32.080 --> 00:17:34.662
And we sort of said to
the guys here in New York,

00:17:34.662 --> 00:17:36.370
do you know the guys
in Sydney and London

00:17:36.370 --> 00:17:38.960
and Montreal that are
researching the same thing?

00:17:38.960 --> 00:17:42.290
And they didn't, in many
cases, know each other existed

00:17:42.290 --> 00:17:43.690
let alone collaborate.

00:17:43.690 --> 00:17:46.405
So a fundamental principle for
us now is around collaboration.

00:17:46.405 --> 00:17:49.320
And typically, the
only thing that gets

00:17:49.320 --> 00:17:52.250
collaborated is a
breakthrough in a journal.

00:17:52.250 --> 00:17:55.010
And what's so
important-- and you guys

00:17:55.010 --> 00:17:57.390
know this-- is sharing
what doesn't work,

00:17:57.390 --> 00:18:00.380
and then people can iterate
off the back of that.

00:18:00.380 --> 00:18:05.080
So Movember's truly
uniquely placed

00:18:05.080 --> 00:18:07.530
to have this influence because
we're in 21 countries now

00:18:07.530 --> 00:18:10.670
with a major funder, so you
get to define the rules,

00:18:10.670 --> 00:18:13.210
haven't you, when you're
handing out these funds.

00:18:13.210 --> 00:18:16.090
And a key principle now
is around collaboration.

00:18:16.090 --> 00:18:20.100
And for us, we want to unite
this research community

00:18:20.100 --> 00:18:22.100
and get them working together.

00:18:22.100 --> 00:18:27.160
And it's quite a cultural
shift for those researchers

00:18:27.160 --> 00:18:28.770
to get to that stage.

00:18:28.770 --> 00:18:30.670
They're normally
used to competing.

00:18:30.670 --> 00:18:32.880
So it's been a really
interesting process.

00:18:32.880 --> 00:18:36.010
And I often think
about this journey,

00:18:36.010 --> 00:18:41.430
